Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.13,0:01:34.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果说宇宙中有一颗行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If there is one planet
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.43,0:01:38.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,象征着美丽 神秘和奇异\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that represents the majesty, mystery and awe of the Universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.58,0:01:41.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那一定是土星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it is Saturn.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.32,0:01:45.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家们也为之激动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It stirs emotion even from scientists who are stunned
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.82,0:01:49.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,被这完美宇宙奇观惊动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by its cosmic perfection.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.94,0:01:59.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你不可否认土星是这宇宙中最美丽的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You've got to hand it to Saturn for being the most beautiful thing out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.01,0:02:03.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星是我最喜欢的行星 我一直用望远镜观察它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's been my favourite planet since I first saw it through the telescope.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.02,0:02:07.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管看起来宁静安详\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}While it looks sleepy and serene,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.73,0:02:10.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这颗太阳系第6行星其实并不平静\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the sixth planet from the Sun is anything but.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.43,0:02:22.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,美丽的外表下隐藏了一个发电机的心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Saturn is a dynamo whose beauty is skin-deep.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.07,0:02:25.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星上极其寒冷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Saturn's an absolutely frigid place.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.55,0:02:28.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不要想着登陆土星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You wouldn't want to step out on the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.36,0:02:29.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,首先它没有固体表面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For one reason, you'd fall 'cause there is no surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.14,0:02:32.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其次也会立即冻死\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but secondly, you'd freeze to death instantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.08,0:02:35.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星是一个大量氢气和氦气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Saturn is a hunk of hydrogen and helium
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.45,0:02:38.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,围绕自轴高速旋转成型的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that races around its axis distorting its shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.57,0:02:45.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,观察专业意大利比萨制作过程\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When you watch a professional toss of pizza,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.09,0:02:48.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,手抛饼底 旋转扁平成型\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as it spins around it flattens out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.43,0:02:52.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,同样的道理 由于很高的旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So it's the same kind of idea, because it's spinning so rapidly
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.30,0:02:56.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星有一点扁平 中间鼓起来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's actually sort of squashed, sort of bulges in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.39,0:02:59.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,称之为"扁球"\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's called an"oblate spheroid".
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.33,0:03:05.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管体型比地球大很多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even though it's much more massive than our own planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.13,0:03:08.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星上的重力比地球还略小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you'd actually weigh slightly less on Saturn that you do on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.02,0:03:14.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个150磅(68千克)的人 在土星上只有137磅(62千克)\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A 150-pound human would weigh only 137 pounds on Saturn.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.90,0:03:19.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是因为土星密度很低\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's because Saturn has such a low density.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.77,0:03:23.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是太阳系中唯一密度低于水的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The only planet in the Solar System less dense than water.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.43,0:03:28.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星如此臃肿\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Saturn is so bloated,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.69,0:03:31.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,绝大部分体积都是气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the gases take up so much space compared to the total amount of mass in Saturn,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.94,0:03:35.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,于是密度低于水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that its density is less than one.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.46,0:03:37.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此假如我们有一个巨大的海\NSo if we could get somehow some…really big ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.73,0:03:43.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把土星放进去 它会飘浮着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in put Saturn in it, it would float.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.66,0:03:52.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,体型上土星是太阳系第二大行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Saturn is the second largest planet in our Solar System.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.59,0:03:54.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是个气体的巨行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It is a gas giant,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.64,0:03:56.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大量的氢和氦\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a mass of hydrogen and helium
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.89,0:03:59.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有地球750倍大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}750 times the size of Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.46,0:04:04.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一天只有10.6个小时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A day on the planet is 10,6 hours long.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.28,0:04:08.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,绕太阳一周需要29.5个地球年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it takes 29.5 Earth years to orbit the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.69,0:04:13.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,拥有48个已命名的卫星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It has 48 named moons.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.74,0:04:23.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星存在于太阳系几乎45亿年了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Saturn has been around for 4.5 billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.58,0:04:27.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,硬质核心由碳颗粒积聚而成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It formed by accreting carbon dust, particle by particle, into a rocky core
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.31,0:04:31.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大约有几个地球大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}several times the size of Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.71,0:04:35.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,吸引着外面大量的氢和氦\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Then, it was able to attract gases, like hydrogen and helium,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.80,0:04:38.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,巨大重力下这些气体坍塌了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which collapsed under gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.78,0:04:44.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由于开始坍塌 气体被压缩\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As things started collapsing, this cloud began to compress,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.67,0:04:46.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,旋转也变的更快\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it began rotating more rapidly,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.71,0:04:51.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,沿自转轴方向上 顶部到底部是不旋转的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but along its axis, from let's say top to bottom, it wasn't rotating,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.75,0:04:54.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此在重力作用下自行坍塌了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so it was free to collapse under the force of gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.02,0:04:59.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,角动量守恒定理\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's called the conservation of angular momentum.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.06,0:05:02.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最初在溜冰场上被展示\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A principle on display at your local ice ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.14,0:05:07.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你伸开你的腿和双臂速度会变慢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you push your arms out if you're an ice skater, you'll go more slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.88,0:05:10.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,收紧你的双臂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you pull your arms in,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.56,0:05:13.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,靠近你的旋转轴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then you'll be more concentrated towards the axis of rotation
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.26,0:05:15.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你会转的更快\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and you'll have to spin faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.60,0:05:22.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,行星在收缩时也会这样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that's just what happens for a planet as it condenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.89,0:05:28.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星在圆盘坍塌过程中旋转起来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A spinning Saturn came out of this collapsed disk.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.73,0:05:35.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星是太阳系中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The feature that has made Saturn the most iconic planet in our Solar System,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.85,0:05:37.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最壮丽的标志\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is its majestic,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.78,0:05:40.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,拥有明亮的光环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}shimmering rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.63,0:05:45.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,光环不可思议的大 直径约173000英里(280000千米)\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They are incredibly big, 173,000 miles in diameter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.89,0:05:49.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比21个地球排列还宽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Wider than 21 Earths side by side.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.36,0:05:57.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,巨大的光环高速旋转 从一端到另一端只需约2天\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So it would take you 2 days in a really fast rocket ship to get from one side of the rings to the other. They're huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.33,0:06:01.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是这些巨大的光环不可思议的薄\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}However, these huge rings also are unbelievably thin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.15,0:06:04.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只有65英尺(20米)厚\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Measuring about 65 feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.75,0:06:08.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果从旁边观看几乎看不到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When viewed from the side, they virtually disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.39,0:06:13.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,厚度大约只相当于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They are no thicker than about one,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.25,0:06:15.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,两层楼高\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}maybe two storeys in a modern day building.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.00,0:06:18.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像一张纸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're paper-thin in comparison.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.36,0:06:22.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看起来像个完美的固体圆盘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The rings may look like perfect solid disks,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.54,0:06:27.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上却是由无数碎片\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}however, they are actually made up of billions of pieces
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.13,0:06:28.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,散布而构成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of space debris.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.22,0:06:36.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,多大的碎片？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But what exactly are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.08,0:06:42.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些大量的冰冷碎片\NThey are countless icy bodies, ranging in size from…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.41,0:06:45.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大的相当于房屋大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}objects as big as houses all the way down to the finest,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.59,0:06:48.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小的仅有犹他州滑雪场的雪花那么大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}powdery snow, you might ski on in Utah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.01,0:06:50.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都由冰块组成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And they're made of water ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.19,0:06:55.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,碎片散布又互相碰撞\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're particles that have been pulverized, so they've smashed into each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.19,0:07:00.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,碎成更小的颗粒\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they've broken up into many, many little particles.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.23,0:07:07.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,呆在土星环里 你会被击成蜂窝\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you were to be inside those rings it would be like a beehive.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.71,0:07:09.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到处都是密布的蜂群\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're all over the place, like bees in a swarm.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.83,0:07:13.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不要派飞船到危险的土星环上去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a hostile place, you do not want to try to put a spacecraft through those rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.41,0:07:17.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些碎片高速旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And these particles spin very fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.71,0:07:22.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,旋转速度大约20000至40000英里每小时(32000至64000千米每小时)\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And they're screaming around the planet at 20 to 40 mph.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.65,0:07:25.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,环内部比环外部的速度快的多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The inner rings spin faster than the outer rings,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.97,0:07:27.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,原因是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and there's a reason for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.11,0:07:33.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,开普勒定理表明--如果以圆形轨道环绕中心旋转 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That if you're gonna orbit in a circle around a central body, Kepler's laws say,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.44,0:07:37.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,越靠近中心旋转越快 越远离中心旋转越慢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if you're close up you move really fast, if you're far away, you move really slow.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.18,0:07:39.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果一颗细沙大小颗粒\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If a particle the size of a grain of sand
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.78,0:07:43.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以超音速击中太空船\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}moving at hypersonic speed were to strike a spacecraft,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.76,0:07:47.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不亚于一枪击中太空船\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it would be like a shotgun blast at point blank range.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.19,0:07:52.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,环外的空间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And you get outside the rings,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.20,0:07:53.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相当宁静\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}things are much quieter.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.75,0:07:56.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果去参观土星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you want to take a country drive around Saturn,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.61,0:07:58.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,请绕过土星环 不要接触它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}go this way,instead of following the rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.16,0:08:05.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为什么说环是土星最神秘之处呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why the rings are there is one of the planet's great mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.06,0:08:08.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,环在很久以前可能是两颗很近卫星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The rings might have once been some of Saturn's moons that got too close
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.95,0:08:12.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,碰撞并碎裂了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and smashed into each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.07,0:08:19.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星的引力维持着这些碎片\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The fractured pieces were held by the planet's gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.21,0:08:21.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,形成土星环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to become its rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.24,0:08:28.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,基于另外一个理论\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}According to another theory,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.92,0:08:31.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许一个巨大的高速物体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}something big and fast might have crashed
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.13,0:08:33.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,撞击了某个土星卫星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into one of Saturn's many moons.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.60,0:08:38.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,碎片被土星引力留下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The broken shards were sucked in by gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.47,0:08:42.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,旋转而形成土星环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and fell into orbit forming the rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.39,0:08:51.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管科学家们对环的形成意见不那么统一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Although scientists disagree as to how the rings were formed,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.08,0:08:54.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对土星环的发现者却没有异议\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they do agree as to who first studied them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.06,0:09:00.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,1610年天文学家伽利略\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In 1610, the Florentine astronomer Galileo Galilei,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.53,0:09:03.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,第一个观测到土星的光环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}first noted the rings of Saturn.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.33,0:09:07.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他看到这些固定在土星周围的光亮物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He saw these little things sticking out on the side of the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.15,0:09:09.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不知道是什么东西 像很多天文学家那样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He had no idea what they were, so like any good astronomer,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.90,0:09:14.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,伽利略记录了他的发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Galileo kept a journal, and he wanted to write into his journal what he had seen,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.75,0:09:16.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是 没有具体说明\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but he didn't have a word for it,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.59,0:09:18.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此他的笔记里没有任何词语说明\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so in his journal, right in with the words,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.11,0:09:23.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只有一幅图示\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he drew in a drawing in place of a noun,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.16,0:09:26.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是他所画的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and this is what he drew.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.21,0:09:30.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星在这里  这两个是他发现的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Here's Saturn, and here's these two things.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.36,0:09:33.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,遗憾的是伽利略并不确切知道这是什么\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Unfortunately Galileo never really figured out what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.83,0:09:37.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只能等今后的天文学家继续探索\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We had to wait for a later astronomer to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.11,0:09:42.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,45年后荷兰物理学家惠更斯\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}45 years later, a Dutch physicist, Christiaan Huygens,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.35,0:09:44.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,找到了答案\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}had an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.20,0:09:50.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他认识到这些不仅仅是一个圆环而是几条圆环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He knew that there wasn't just one ring, but several giant rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.31,0:09:55.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如今我们知道里面有7个环区\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Today, there are seven know ring regions.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.28,0:10:00.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A环B环C环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's the A-ring, the B-ring and the C-ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.44,0:10:02.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是3个最主要的环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So those are the three main rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.91,0:10:05.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,C环里面还有D环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There is a ring interior to the C-ring called the D-ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.01,0:10:10.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当我们的先驱者号到达土星 发现了最美丽的F环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And once we got there with Voyager, showed us the F-ring in all its glory.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.14,0:10:13.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在F环外还有微弱的E环和G环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And then there were some diffuse rings outside, the E and the G-ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.00,0:10:19.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每条环的性质都不一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Each of these rings has a different personality.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.09,0:10:21.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A环几乎是透明的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The A-ring is almost transparent,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.29,0:10:24.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为光线最容易穿透A环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is why light easily passes through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.71,0:10:27.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,B环密度最大 充满物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The B-ring is dense, chock-full of material.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.34,0:10:32.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,C环比A环还透明\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The C-ring is even more transparent than the A.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.36,0:10:35.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而那儿是D环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}While the D-ring is barely there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.46,0:10:38.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些环里面有许多令人感兴趣的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's a lot of neat things in those rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.58,0:10:41.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们认为他们都是不同的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So you can't think of them as homogeneous body.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.34,0:10:45.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你可以想象一下这些由各种碎片组成的环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You gotta think of  each particle inside those rings and what is ***
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.39,0:10:50.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像我们所见颜色 形状和阴影各不相同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These distinct qualities are what we see as colours, shapes and shadows.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.08,0:10:53.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,神奇的土星光环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The wonder that is Saturn's rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.61,0:11:04.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们能够看见它是因为\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The reason we can see them at all is due to the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.89,0:11:08.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它像月亮一样反射阳光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just as our moon glows with reflected sunlight,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.23,0:11:11.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是土星光环如此明亮的原因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So these Saturn's rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.30,0:11:14.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个现象称为环反射\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It is a phenomenon called"ring shine".
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.00,0:11:18.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,想象一下你在土星背面的黑夜中抬头仰望\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just imagine yourself on the night side of Saturn looking up,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.75,0:11:23.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看见这些光环布满整个天空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and having the rings just completely covering the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.23,0:11:28.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比地球上的满月亮很多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so do Saturn's rings. It's much brighter than ** the Earth on a full moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.39,0:11:34.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,闪耀着 非常明亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They shimmer, and they're brilliant and they're bright,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.99,0:11:37.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这主要是由于环由冰质碎片组成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that's because they're mostly made up of ice particles
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.16,0:11:39.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,反射了更多的阳光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which reflect a lot of sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.94,0:11:43.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而有迹象表明\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}However, there is evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.92,0:11:45.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种太阳系奇观\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the glowing marvels of our Solar System
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.95,0:11:48.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许不是永恒的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}won't be around forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.94,0:11:53.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一些科学家猜测光环可能在某时消失\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some scientists are asking just when will they disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.93,0:12:10.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管科学家们对于土星光环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For all scientists know about Saturn's rings,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.61,0:12:12.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,依然还有很多不明之处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they remain a huge mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.01,0:12:17.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种猜想也受到质疑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When they appeared is a point of much debate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.43,0:12:21.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们认为环形成于土星诞生时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists used to believe that the rings were formed at the same time as Saturn.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.08,0:12:24.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,约45亿年前\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}4.5 billion years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.09,0:12:29.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是我们无法知道环上的物质 还有哪些是最初形成时的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But because we don't understand what holds the rings together
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.31,0:12:33.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们最多只能猜测环还能坚持多久\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and our best guess as to how long the rings could stay together
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.28,0:12:37.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许还能存在几亿年吧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is only a hundred million years, there's something wrong with this picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.24,0:12:41.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有理由相信\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are reasons to believe
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.96,0:12:44.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星环的寿命不会超过几亿年了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they're no older than a few hundred million years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.48,0:12:47.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个理由出自\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Those reasons lie in trying to estimate
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.50,0:12:50.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对环磨损消耗速度的预计\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}how much erosion is taking place on the rings,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.69,0:12:53.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为小陨石的不断袭击\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because of the hailstorm of micro-meteorites,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.99,0:12:58.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些高速飞来的微小陨石\Nsmall, tiny bodies… particles
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.38,0:13:01.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,袭击并损耗土星环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that come in at a tremendous speed and chip away at the rings and therefore erode them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.44,0:13:05.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天王星 海王星和木星都有自己的环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Neptune, Uranus and Jupiter also have rings,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.90,0:13:07.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只是比较少和微弱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but theirs are sparse and dim.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.95,0:13:12.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星环是最明亮完整的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Saturn's are bright and full,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.24,0:13:13.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这导致科学家们思索\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}leading scientists to suggest
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.81,0:13:17.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星环可能没有被侵蚀太久\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that they haven't been exposed to erosion for long.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.85,0:13:21.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也就是说 相对还很新\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And therefore are relatively new.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.05,0:13:25.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是 不断的侵蚀\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But, does this gradual erosion
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.13,0:13:28.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是否意味着土星最终将失去着最大的特征？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}mean that Saturn will lose its most magnificent feature?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.64,0:13:33.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种想法认为长时间以来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The idea is that over long periods of time
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.35,0:13:36.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,环的物质碎片将越来越碎小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the material can get just so small that it can be charged,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.52,0:13:41.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你进入土星的磁力层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and acquiring a charge in Saturn's magnetosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.63,0:13:46.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会被磁力场拉出土星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then it can just get zipped away, taken away by the magnetic field.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.08,0:13:55.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或者直接螺旋形掉进土星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Or it just spirals into Saturn itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.40,0:14:00.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是土星环的死亡阶段\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That is a scenario for the death of the rings,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.95,0:14:02.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将被慢慢消耗掉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's that they finally get eroded away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.99,0:14:05.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此土星环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In order for Saturn to continuously have rings,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.86,0:14:08.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,需要不断的补充\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they need to be re-filled.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.19,0:14:13.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当前的土星环如此巨大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For the moment Saturn has a tremendously large ring system,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.86,0:14:18.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但环的组成物质需要不断补充\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but the actual material in the rings does have to be replenished.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.92,0:14:24.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样看来 另一种形式的袭击似乎是必须的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Strangely, another kind of assault might be necessary
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.27,0:14:26.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,才能维持环的存在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to preserve them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.29,0:14:30.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,必须要有彗星击中土星环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They have to get renewed by an errant comet coming in and crashing,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.83,0:14:35.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,给环提供新的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}adding to the mass that's going around there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.75,0:14:38.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个问题备受怀疑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The debate continues
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.68,0:14:46.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,环消失的理论在建立过程中始终充满争议\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when theorising as to when the ring will vanish.And that kind of question is still being debated.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.87,0:14:51.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,需要几亿年或几十亿年 我不能确定\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hundreds of millions of years, probably, maybe billions of years, we don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.26,0:14:53.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个课题一直在讨论中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's a matter of debate right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.23,0:14:56.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,环到底是很年轻 然后很快就死亡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Whether the rings are young and are gonna die an early death,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.33,0:15:01.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还是已经存在很久了 也将继续存在很久很久\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or they're old and they're gonna remain with us for a very, very long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.21,0:15:10.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星的48颗卫星中 某些小卫星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Of Saturn's 48 named moons, there are small moons
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.25,0:15:12.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,被称作"牧羊犬"卫星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}called"shepherds", for a good reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.34,0:15:18.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,引力作用下他们围绕着某条土星环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They have gravitational pulls that help keep the rings intact
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.36,0:15:20.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,放牧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by herding the particles.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.11,0:15:28.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星专家们被这土星的卫星和环之间复杂精巧的编排所吸引\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Saturn's experts are interested in the complicated choreography between the planet's moons and its rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.57,0:15:33.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,扭曲麻花般的F环特别引人关注\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The contorted F-ring is especially intriguing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.05,0:15:40.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,两个牧羊犬卫星环绕在两边 普罗米修斯(土卫16)和潘多拉(土卫17)\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And then there's the two shepherd satellites on either side, Prometheus and Pandora,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.28,0:15:43.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,环被卫星引力作用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they are having gravitational effects on this ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.83,0:15:45.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,拉向几个方向\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's being tugged in a variety of directions,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.23,0:15:50.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看起来影响非常剧烈\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so it looks wild and misbehaved, if you will,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.81,0:15:53.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是动力变化作用区域\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it's a dynamicists playground.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.37,0:15:58.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们对F环发生的这一切非常感兴趣\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're very, very interested in watching what happens to the F-ring
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.61,0:16:02.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为这展示了卫星与环之间的相互作用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because it tells us how moons interact with rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.63,0:16:09.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星早在公元前700年的古文明中被记载\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Saturn mesmerized civilizations as early as 700 BCE,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.95,0:16:16.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,亚述人记录了星空中明亮的土星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when the Assyrians took note of it sparkling in the distant sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.69,0:16:21.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,数百年后希腊人称之(克洛诺斯)\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hundreds of years later, the Greeks gave it a name: Cronos,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.93,0:16:23.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,收获之神\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}after the god of harvest.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.84,0:16:27.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可能由于土星在收获的季节里处于天堂的位置\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Possibly due to its position in the sky during harvest season.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.09,0:16:32.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星又是罗马神话的农业之神\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Romans' god of agriculture was Saturnus,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.66,0:16:34.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是现在土星的含义\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is why we call it Saturn.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.01,0:16:37.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也是由一星期的第六天来命名\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They also named a day of the week after him,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.46,0:16:40.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,英语里的星期六\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what we now call Saturday.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.14,0:16:43.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过 如果罗马人近距离观察土星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}However, had the Romans actually seen the planet close up,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.99,0:16:47.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可能会称之为天气之神\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they might have named it for the god of weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.70,0:16:58.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星是一个狂热之处 时刻变化着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Saturn is a wild, ever-changing place but,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.77,0:17:00.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不像地球上的天气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}unlike on Earth where things change
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.97,0:17:03.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通常只持续几天或几小时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on a daily and even on an hourly basis,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.39,0:17:07.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星风暴能持续几天 几周甚至几个月\Nthe storms on Saturn can last for days and weeks and months…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.46,0:17:11.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,缓慢变化的巨大范围的天气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and things change on a large scale very slowly over time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.47,0:17:23.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星剧烈天气现象的发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The discovery of this violent activity on Saturn
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.73,0:17:25.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,惊动了专家们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}came as a surprise to experts.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.13,0:17:30.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,几个世纪以来 对土星的观测都不是那么清晰\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For centuries, their view of the planet had been obscured
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.48,0:17:32.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星大气中的大片氨气阻碍了观测\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by an ammonia gas haze.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.89,0:17:38.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,新的卫星数据改变了这一切\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}New satellite data is changing everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.61,0:17:43.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在我们知道土星活力十足\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we see now that Saturn is a dynamic place.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.67,0:17:46.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,被证明甚至比木星还要活跃的多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's been revealed now as being probably more dynamic in a lot of ways than Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.06,0:17:50.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,仅仅就我们已经看到的那些风暴\NThere's the number of storms we see, the motions that they do…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.62,0:17:56.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,风暴的风速达到惊人的1000英里每小时(1600千米每小时)\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Incredibly, winds blow at speeds of 1,000 mph.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.22,0:18:00.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际的测量风暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We measure the winds literally
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.00,0:18:04.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,需要观察小块的气体移动图像\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by watching the different little cells of the atmosphere move in imaging.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.63,0:18:06.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此从拍摄的图像\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So you need sequential images
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.97,0:18:09.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看看这些是怎样快速移动的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to see how much things have moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.51,0:18:11.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星表面没有山\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are no mountains on the surface of Saturn,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.89,0:18:14.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,仔细看看这些云的面貌\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}its cloud features that we look at to see how quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.89,0:18:18.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如何快速地变化 运动形成飓风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they evolve and change and move to measure the winds.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.01,0:18:21.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最近的探索显示出\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Recent exploration has shown
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.73,0:18:23.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一些目前难以理解的现象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}other phenomena that aren't yet understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.16,0:18:28.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们可以看见这些面貌 云团和漩涡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We can see features, clouds, eddies,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.65,0:18:33.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,像木星上那样的巨大的条状物体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}big plumes of material like we see on Jupiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.60,0:18:37.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以看见其中的很多椭圆风暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we see these oval storms, lots of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.88,0:18:40.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上在南半球的这个纬度段里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and in fact is one latitude in the Southern hemisphere
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.84,0:18:43.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有许多风暴\Nwhere lots of storms zip around…disband,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.02,0:18:47.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以观测到他们的产生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we've watched them be created,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.11,0:18:50.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以看到其中一些合并消失了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we've seen them die, they die by merging.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.98,0:18:54.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家们昵称之风暴巷道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists nicknamed this area"Storm Alley",
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.37,0:18:56.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有半个美国西边大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}after a region in America's Midwest
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.67,0:18:59.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,造成剧烈气象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that produces violent weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.66,0:19:06.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相信这里也存在着闪电\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It is believed there's lightning there,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.72,0:19:09.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过目前还没有被发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}though no one has seen it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.02,0:19:13.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是因为技术上的原因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And there's a technical reason for that,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.35,0:19:16.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,闪电需要在黑夜中观察\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to see the lightning you'd have to get around on the night side,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.65,0:19:19.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为闪电的亮度不是太大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and because the lightning ** aren't all that bright,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.05,0:19:21.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,必须在黑暗中观察\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so you need the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.94,0:19:24.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是土星的黑夜十分明亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the night side of Saturn is very bright
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.26,0:19:26.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由于土星光环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because of all the ring light
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.36,0:19:30.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把土星夜晚照耀得如此明亮\Nthat shines down on the night side of Saturn and so…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.96,0:19:35.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要辨别云层中的闪电十分困难\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's very hard to sort the lightning from just puffy little clouds.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.31,0:19:41.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星大气更是令人惊奇\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The hellish weather on Saturn has one more astounding surprise,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.65,0:19:46.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,简直就是个怪物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and is a true monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.97,0:19:50.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,某个土星奇异风暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One of the freakiest storms on Saturn
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.74,0:19:54.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,南极上的飓风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was this hurricane-like thing that they found down at the South pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.54,0:19:57.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,风暴面积比美国还大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This storm is bigger than the US.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.75,0:20:01.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而木星上的那个大红斑也是风暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The great red spot on Jupiter is merely hurricane-like.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.23,0:20:04.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是个没有眼的风暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That storm doesn't have an eyewall.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.05,0:20:10.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而这个南极土星大风暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}However, the South pole storm
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.21,0:20:13.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,跟地球上的飓风特点一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has the characteristics of a terrestrial hurricane,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.58,0:20:15.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它有个眼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}including an eyewall,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.40,0:20:19.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是地球外唯一的有眼风暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}making it the only such storm on another planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.17,0:20:23.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还不确切是否是跟地球上一样的飓风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's not clear that it is a hurricane in every sense like we have here on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.51,0:20:27.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过目前从形态上来看\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But so far, the morphology of it
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.21,0:20:29.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,非常像一个地球飓风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}looks very much like a hurricane.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.10,0:20:32.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这非常令人激动  每个人都为之兴奋不已\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That was very exciting, everyone got very excited about that,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.22,0:20:33.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们被震惊了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it even surprised us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.26,0:20:38.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你可以从这个飓风眼中看过去就像在地球上那样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And you can see right down into the eye, just as you can with a hurricane on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.98,0:20:41.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能看到土星大气中更多的气象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they can see farther into Saturn's atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.59,0:20:43.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些一直经常发生的气象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than they've ever been able to see before.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.86,0:20:47.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这真是土星之窗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So this thing is literally a window into Saturn.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.14,0:20:49.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很惊人的发现一些气象与地球上的十分相似\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it's amazing to see something so similar to Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.86,0:20:53.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们可以对之做一些研究\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on Saturn and then find out that we can actually do some science because of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.44,0:20:57.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,南极大风暴据测有5000英里(8000千米)宽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The South pole storm measures 5,000 mile across,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.51,0:21:00.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,2/3个地球的直径大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's 2/3 the diameter of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.07,0:21:06.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果一个极其强大的风暴产生于地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If a hurricane that huge were to form here,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.17,0:21:09.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,距离跨越纽约到巴格达\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it would cover a distance from New York city to Baghdad,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.89,0:21:12.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将摧毁这之间的一切\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}annihilating all in its path.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.35,0:21:22.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,飓风围绕其中心的眼漩涡型旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It basically is a swirling vortex of air that is centred around a hole,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.06,0:21:26.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像围墙围着这个中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and right at the centre, where with an eyewall around it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.34,0:21:31.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还不知道是什么导致这么巨大的风暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What powers this monster storm is still unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.67,0:21:34.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星的风暴比地球上强大很多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the winds are stronger on Saturn than they are in Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.48,0:21:36.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这真是一个迷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is a puzzle in itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.82,0:21:40.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星受到的太阳能很低 自身也没有释放多少能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because Saturn gets so little energy from either the Sun or from its own inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.51,0:21:45.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,风暴发生在南极中央而不是赤道附近\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's centred around the South pole of Saturn rather than being
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.90,0:21:49.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,异于地球上的风暴\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the equatorial region, like a hurricane on Earth would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.81,0:21:53.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,2007年初现代图像采集技术\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In early 2007, modern imaging technology
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.37,0:21:57.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,揭示了更多土星上令科学家们震惊的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}revealed something else on Saturn that astounded scientists.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.35,0:22:00.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们对它兴趣更浓了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We see it very intensely now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.48,0:22:05.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它如此大和奇怪\NIt's something big, something strange…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.48,0:22:09.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我从来没有在宇宙其他地方见过\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and something never seen in the Universe before.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.31,0:22:23.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星 太阳系中奇怪而又最美丽的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Saturn, the Solar System's most bizarre yet beautiful planet
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.12,0:22:27.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,越来越充满了神秘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has just gotten even more mysterious.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.08,0:22:32.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,1979年先驱者号探测器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In 1979, the Voyager spacecraft
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.52,0:22:36.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,显示出土星北极的完美几何形状\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}showed a perfect geometric form over the North Pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.69,0:22:39.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,2006年10月\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In October 2006,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.99,0:22:43.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,卡西尼探测器发现它还在那儿\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Cassini craft found that it is still there.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.20,0:22:49.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很奇怪它还在那儿 没有移动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's just bizarre. It sits there kind of still, it doesn't move with the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.67,0:22:52.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,极地形似一个六边形\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Pole has a hexagonal feature,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.43,0:22:56.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,6条边围绕着北极\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a six-sided polygon that encircles the pole
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.62,0:22:58.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大约在北纬78度的位置\Nat about 78°North latitude,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.99,0:23:01.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,特点就是 它一直固定在那儿\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it's sitting there as a set feature.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.19,0:23:10.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这六边形有点像地球上的极地漩涡\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The hexagon is similar to Earth's polar vortex
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.93,0:23:14.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,长时间固定形状地在极地周围吹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which has winds blowing in a circular fashion around the pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.85,0:23:20.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星漩涡大到可以塞下4个地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Saturn's vortex can fit 4 Earths inside of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.48,0:23:24.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在土星云层里延伸60英里深\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and extends 60 miles deep into Saturn's clouds.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.07,0:23:30.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,非常奇怪的是航海者号发现一小片云在其中100/米秒旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And what's more bizarre, Voyager saw little, tiny clouds going around at about 100 meters per second,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.09,0:23:34.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以200英里每小时(320千米每小时)的速度在六边形里旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is about 200 mph, going around this racetrack.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.36,0:23:36.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,专家认为这只是一种短暂的现象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}People thought,"Well, maybe they're just a temporary thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.58,0:23:37.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那儿的漩涡怎么形成的？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}"how could this stay there?"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.63,0:23:41.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在那里持续了至少20年 这到底是什么？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's stayed there now for at least 20 years, and we're going,"What is this?"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.76,0:23:56.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果在那儿 你钻进土星厚云层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you go there you're gonna enter these thick clouds,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.34,0:24:02.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,越深气体密度越大 大气压越强\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the deeper you go the more intense the pressure's gonna get,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.39,0:24:04.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,超过某个深度你会内爆\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to a point when you just implode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.48,0:24:09.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你和你的太空船无法继续前进\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You and your spacecraft can't make it any farther.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.01,0:24:26.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,目前探测器环绕土星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For now, visits to Saturn's orbit
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.09,0:24:28.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,作为土星的人造卫星使用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are reserved for unmanned spacecrafts.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.45,0:24:32.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里至少已经有48颗天然卫星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But surrounding the planet are at least 48 moons.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.49,0:24:35.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,冒险登陆某个卫星则具有可行性\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Venturing to one of those is more feasible.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.77,0:24:39.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们去土星的一个大兴趣点\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What's interesting now that we're going to these planets,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.93,0:24:42.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是探索那些卫星们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is that we're learning that in some ways
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.74,0:24:45.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,热闹的卫星大团聚\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the moons are where the action is.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.94,0:24:48.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们去过了其中的一个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We've already been to one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.00,0:24:55.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,提坦(土卫六)是除了月球外 唯一探索过的卫星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Titan is the only moon other than our own to have been explored.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.41,0:24:59.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这次探索意义非常重大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The event was beyond significant.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.32,0:25:03.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,2005年1月14日\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On January 14th, 2005,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.35,0:25:06.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科幻成为了现实\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}science-fiction became fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.04,0:25:10.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,作为正在土星执行的卡西尼任务的一部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As part of the ongoing Cassini mission to Saturn,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.16,0:25:12.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,惠更斯号无人探测器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the unmanned Huygens probe
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.50,0:25:15.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,降落到这个最大土星卫星表面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}descended onto the surface of Saturn's biggest moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.69,0:25:22.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,提坦(土卫六)星如其名 有水星那么大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Titan lives up to its name. It is the size of the planet Mercury.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.46,0:25:26.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上是太阳系中第二大的卫星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In fact, it is the second largest moon in the Solar System.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.45,0:25:29.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比月球大一半\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}50% bigger than our Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.79,0:25:36.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很多方面都吸引着人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It is seductive in many ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.82,0:25:41.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一方面土卫六非常像地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For one, Titan looks much like Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.28,0:25:45.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,过程非常让我激动 \NThat was the thing that beat me over the head, just how…
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.10,0:25:49.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,逐渐接近土卫六的地面的过程\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}remarkably similar in process the surface of Titan looked.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.60,0:26:03.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看见的河流 湖床 还有风\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We have river channels that feed into these lake beds, we have winds.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.08,0:26:12.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来另个区域又看见了沙丘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And then in other areas we have dunes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.08,0:26:21.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在土卫六的赤道地区\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The equator region of Titan,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.14,0:26:25.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,收到了质量很高的雷达图像\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at least on one side where we've gotten good radar imagery,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.13,0:26:28.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,数百个隔着数百英里的沙丘\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has hundreds and hundreds of miles of these dunes,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.05,0:26:32.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,沙丘有几百米高 分别隔着几英里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that are hundreds of meters high, several miles apart,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.27,0:26:37.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,简直就是沙丘海洋\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they just go on, this vast sea of dunes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.03,0:26:52.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许是固体碳氢化合物颗粒堆积成的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are possibly deposits of solid hydro-carbons.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.96,0:26:57.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只有等探测器降落下去了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we didn't really know until that probe landed
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.20,0:27:00.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,才知道到底是降落在液态还是固态地表上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}whether it was gonna hit liquid or some solid surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.83,0:27:04.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看起来像掉到了布丁上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It seemed to kind of fall on what looks like a kind of pudding,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.59,0:27:07.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,既不是液态也不是固态\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it doesn't seem to be liquid or solid.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.81,0:27:14.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土卫六的表面似乎附着一些粘稠物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It seems that Titan has some goo on the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.99,0:27:17.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,既不是陆地也不是海\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's almost kind of neither land nor sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.58,0:27:20.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而是介于其间的 非常令人惊讶\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but something in between. That's very amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.98,0:27:28.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,惊奇的是土卫六像地球一样有着大气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Amazingly, Titan, like Earth, has an extended atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.57,0:27:33.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳系没有其他任何卫星有大气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No other moon does in our Solar System.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.15,0:27:46.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土卫六大气很浓密很厚\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The atmosphere of Titan is very, very thick and massive.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.71,0:27:51.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是地球大气的10倍质量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It has a mass that's 10 times the mass of the Earth's atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.17,0:27:54.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是一层非常非常厚的气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So you have a very thick layer of gases,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.20,0:27:56.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比其他我们所知道的大气都要厚\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}thicker than the air as we know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.01,0:27:59.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大气中的微粒十分小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The particles in the air are also very small,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.03,0:28:02.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使得看起来比较模糊\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so I would characterize them more .
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.98,0:28:04.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,像雾或者云那样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as a haze than as a fog or clouds
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.46,0:28:12.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雾有200英里(320千米)厚 完全不同与地球上的云\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The haze is 200 miles thick resembling something else on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.94,0:28:23.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从外面看上去像一个完全不透明的大桔子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}From the outside, it appears essentially opaque, like a big, orange ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.02,0:28:28.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是随着惠更斯探测器穿越大气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But as the Huygens probe descended through the atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.77,0:28:31.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,开始变得透明起来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's transparent enough
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.47,0:28:33.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以看清降落区域的地表特征\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to be able to see the surface features as it fell through.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.55,0:28:38.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,跟洛杉矶的大雾没有太大不同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it's not unlike a hazy day here in Los Angeles.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.30,0:28:43.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不是土卫六大气的颜色吸引科学家\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's not the colour of the atmosphere that most intrigues scientists,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.07,0:28:47.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而是其成分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's the composition.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.84,0:28:51.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,氮气和甲烷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Nitrogen and methane,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.73,0:28:54.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,正是早期地球大气的主要成分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the same gases they believe made up much of Earth's early atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.88,0:28:57.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,认为土卫六的大气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The idea that Titan's atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.99,0:29:01.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,跟40亿年前的地球大气很相似\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}mimics the atmosphere of early Earth 4 billion years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.12,0:29:04.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,激动着我们 让人很兴奋\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's something we're very, very excited about and interested in.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.55,0:29:07.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是我们在实验室做过的最困难的实验\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it's one of the things we're studying very hard in our laboratory.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.55,0:29:09.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看看是否能得到期待的结果\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Let's see if we can get this aligned. What do we have?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.05,0:29:14.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科罗拉多州立大学 玛格丽特·托尔伯特博士\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At the University of Colorado, Dr. Margaret Tolbert
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.41,0:29:17.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,正在她的实验室里模拟土卫六大气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is simulating Titan's atmosphere in her lab.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.93,0:29:22.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是否其中包含着生命形成所需的元素？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Might it too have the necessary ingredients for life?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.73,0:29:27.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这个实验里 尽量模拟土卫六\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In this experiment we're trying to simulate the chemistry
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.44,0:29:30.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大气顶部的气体成分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that goes on high in Titan's atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.14,0:29:31.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也就是大雾之处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where the haze is forming.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.04,0:29:34.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里有个反应室\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So what we have is a reaction chamber here,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.64,0:29:38.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,里面充满了氮气和甲烷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and all that we have here is nitrogen and methane.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.04,0:29:41.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土卫六大气的主要成分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So the two most important components of Titan's atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.14,0:29:45.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后我们只亮一盏灯\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And then we're just gonna flick on a lamp,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.06,0:29:49.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这盏灯模拟太阳照射到土卫六大气上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that lamp is going to simulate the sunlight hitting Titan's atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.06,0:29:52.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,托尔伯特博士的研究令人惊讶地 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Incredibly, Tolbert's research has shown
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.34,0:29:54.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,显示出土卫六的大气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that Titan's atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.68,0:29:57.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在模拟的阳光下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when stimulated by sunlight,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.08,0:29:59.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,开始产生一些有机化合物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}begins to produce organic compounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.38,0:30:04.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这对于科学家在地球外寻找生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For scientists looking for life beyond our planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.38,0:30:07.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,非常的有帮助\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}this could be big.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.91,0:30:21.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当科学家们在银河系里寻找生命的迹象时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As scientists scour the galaxy for signs of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.71,0:30:25.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些令人激动的结果来自太阳系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there are some exciting results from within our own Solar System.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.31,0:30:33.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土卫六应该含有这些生命必需的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Saturn's moon, Titan, seems to have the necessary ingredients.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.61,0:30:42.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科罗拉多州立大学的实验表明阳光和富含氮气 甲烷的土卫六大气共同作用\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Testing at the University of Colorado has shown that when sunlight interacts with Titan's nitrogen and methane-rich atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.06,0:30:45.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,产生有机化合物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}organic compounds are created.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.52,0:30:48.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些有机物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So these organics are
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.04,0:30:50.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,飘浮在土卫六表面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}floating down to the surface of Titan,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.76,0:30:53.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像图片中那些\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and you can see them in the pictures,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.26,0:30:56.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,谁又知道这些化合物会创造出什么呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and who knows what they're doing once they're there?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.36,0:30:59.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许能创造某些新形式的生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They could be providing energy to some new kind of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.46,0:31:04.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还需要做更多的研究\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Further research is needed
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.09,0:31:06.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,测定土卫六上是否真的有生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to determine if there really is life on Titan.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.36,0:31:09.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或者能在某时进化出生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Or if it might some day develop.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.86,0:31:12.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管土卫六大气非常相似早期地球大气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Although its atmosphere resembles early Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.96,0:31:15.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但还是有很大不同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the environment is vastly different.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.56,0:31:20.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里很冷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.66,0:31:22.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,低于零下华氏300度(-150度)\NIt's -300 ℉
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.47,0:31:23.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有液态水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and there's no liquid water.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.78,0:31:26.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是土卫六和早期地球的最大不同\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So that's a big difference between early Earth and Titan.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.15,0:31:30.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土卫六上的河床和湖床\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The lakes and river beds on Titan
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.45,0:31:32.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是另外一些东西开凿的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}were carved down to the ground by something.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.35,0:31:35.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里没有液态水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's no liquid water on the moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.85,0:31:37.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么 是什么在这里流动？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so what flows on this terrain?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.15,0:31:42.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球上的山是硅酸盐石块构成\NThe hills on Earth are made of silicate, rocks…
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.55,0:31:46.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而土卫六上的山由冰和固态甲烷构成\Nwhereas the hills on Titan are ice, methane ice…
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.15,0:31:50.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,河道是甲烷雨造成的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The river channels on Titan are formed by methane rain,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.85,0:31:54.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不同于地球上流水形成的河谷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as opposed to the Earth river valleys formed by water.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.45,0:32:00.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,显然 这里下着液态的甲烷雨\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Liquid methane, it seems, rains down on Titan,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.15,0:32:03.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或者曾经下过\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or did at one time.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.25,0:32:08.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土卫六温度太低一些气体都液化了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On Titan, it is so cold that gases liquefied.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.75,0:32:12.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就有了河流湖泊\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And there are coastlines and rivers,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.85,0:32:18.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些地面河流都由\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and all this terrain shaped
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.25,0:32:21.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,液态甲烷构成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by moving rivers of methane.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.45,0:32:25.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些非常令人好奇\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's just completely intriguing.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.35,0:32:31.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甲烷是天然气的主要成分  还包含一些丙烷和丁烷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Methane is the principal component of natural gas, butane and propane.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.55,0:32:34.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都是能源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All sources of fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.25,0:32:37.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,含碳油气都是燃料\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's a lot of hydrocarbons,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.33,0:32:41.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星六上发现的就是这些\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it might be very light hydrocarbons, on Titan.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.15,0:32:42.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,含量很多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And there's a lot of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.85,0:32:45.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只要有氧可以永远燃烧下去\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it burns if you put it in contact with oxygen,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.75,0:32:47.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那里能量非常之多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so there's a lot of energy out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.75,0:32:51.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,卫星表面的这么多能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Enough on the surface of this huge moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.47,0:32:55.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以满足很长时间人类的需求\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to supply all of Earth's needs for a very long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.75,0:33:00.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土卫六天然气储量非常大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Here is this tremendous supply of natural gas on Titan.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.85,0:33:03.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能都带回地球那就太棒了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well, wouldn't it be great to go out there and tap into it and bring it back?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.85,0:33:08.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但我想这将耗资巨大\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But I think that you would find that it would cost you so much to go out
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.27,0:33:09.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把甲烷提取并带回来\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and get the methane and bring it back,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.99,0:33:14.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上你带不回任何东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that you would never be able to effectively power anything on Earth with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.05,0:33:20.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管土卫六是土星最大的卫星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}While Titan is Saturn's largest moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.55,0:33:23.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过某个小卫星也许更令人激动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one of its smallest may be even more exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.85,0:33:28.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土卫二 由明亮的冰岩混合组成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a brilliant ball of ice and rock called Enceladus.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.95,0:33:33.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它比较小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a tiny object,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.45,0:33:36.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直径只有300英里(480千米)\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's only about 300 miles in size.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.75,0:33:39.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,体积只有月球的1/8\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's about 1/8th the size of our own Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.05,0:33:42.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们从没见过如此小的天体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we've never seen a body that small
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.15,0:33:45.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,居然是活跃的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that has activity on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.65,0:33:50.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,2005年发现了它的活力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This activity was discovered in 2005
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.15,0:33:55.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由卡西尼成像团队的卡罗林·帕科博士发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by Dr. Carolyn Porco and her Cassini imaging team.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.35,0:34:00.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一幅照片上显示土卫二像个喷气式发动机\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One photo seemed to suggest that jets were coming out of Enceladus.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.25,0:34:05.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在我们团队看来很可能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It seemed very likely to the members of my team that it's possible
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.27,0:34:07.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个喷气式发动机是个间歇喷泉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that these jets are actually geysers,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.55,0:34:09.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,喷射水汽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they're erupting from pockets of liquid water
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.45,0:34:12.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,喷气位置离表面不深\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}not too far beneath the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.55,0:34:23.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球上与土卫二最相近的应该是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The closest thing we have on Earth to Enceladus
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.85,0:34:27.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黄石国家公园的老实间歇泉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is something like Old Faithful geyser here at Yellowstone National Park,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.55,0:34:31.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能把水汽喷上约100英尺(45米)高\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is shooting water vapour and water about 150 ft into the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.45,0:34:35.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而土卫二上的蒸汽喷泉能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The geysers on Enceladus are erupting
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.95,0:34:37.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在空中喷出几百英里高\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}water vapour hundreds or miles into the air
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.05,0:34:41.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是由于喷射猛烈而又没有大气阻碍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because there's much lower gravity there and the fact there's no atmosphere holding them in.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.15,0:34:48.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土卫二上被发现的很多喷泉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Many geysers have since been discovered,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.53,0:34:51.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都位于南半球的一个区域内\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all in a region of Enceladus' southern hemisphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.75,0:34:54.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,产生于那些裂缝\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They are coming out of these fissures,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.81,0:34:58.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些巨大裂缝延伸有135千米长\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}big cracks that go on for about 135 kilometres.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.65,0:35:01.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一些80英里长的裂缝\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Something like 80 miles of cracks.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.55,0:35:06.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们称之"老虎纹"\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We call them"tiger stripes",
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.96,0:35:08.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为我们第一次看见的时候\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because when we first saw them
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.73,0:35:10.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,发现这些纹路非常像老虎身上的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they really looked like the stripes on a tiger.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.55,0:35:13.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有4个区域布满裂缝\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There're four areas that seem to be ridges
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.29,0:35:17.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,应该都是地质活跃地区\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or kind of active geologic areas.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.75,0:35:19.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些区域喷射的水汽柱\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the plumes seemed to be coming out of these areas
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.15,0:35:22.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大约有20或21根\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we counted about 20 or 21 plumes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.95,0:35:27.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土卫二的南面都被宇宙级的老实泉覆盖\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Southern Enceladus is covered in cosmic Old Faithfuls.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.55,0:35:32.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,谁能想到一个德克萨斯州大的冰球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Who would have thought that an ice ball of the size of Texas
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.75,0:35:35.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,活力十足 不停喷发水柱和水汽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would be alive with plumes and geysers?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.35,0:35:37.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太令人惊异了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I mean, it's astounding.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.15,0:35:43.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土卫二由于土星的潮汐作用而被加热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Enceladus is heated in its interior by the tides of Saturn.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.15,0:35:46.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,月球引力作用于地球海洋\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Earth's Moon is pulling on the Earth's oceans
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.65,0:35:49.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,拉升而造成潮汐现象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and distorting their shape and producing the tides
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.21,0:35:51.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些现象我们很熟悉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that we're familiar with here on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.55,0:35:56.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过土卫二在土星强大引力作用下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But on Enceladus, the planet Saturn is pulling on that moon
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.57,0:35:58.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在围绕土星旋转的同时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and as Enceladus goes around in its orbit,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.77,0:36:02.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由于引力方向不断变化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that pull is changing the ice inside Enceladus.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.30,0:36:04.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土卫二内部不断碎裂摩擦\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's creaking and groaning and rubbing against itself
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.20,0:36:07.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,产生大量热量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and creating a lot of heat through friction.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.50,0:36:11.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们认为这潮汐摩擦生成的热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We think it's that frictional heat
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.70,0:36:15.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,使冰水蒸发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that is producing the evaporation of the water ice that
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.20,0:36:20.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从地表裂缝中逃逸 形成了我们所见的喷泉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is then escaping through these cracks and making the geysers that we see there.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.42,0:36:23.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,另外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And there's more.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.89,0:36:28.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土卫二的喷发 证实了另一个理论\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Enceladus' eruptions have clarified a theory
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.93,0:36:31.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,关于土星某个环的形成原因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of what powers one of Saturn's rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.50,0:36:34.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们了解到土卫二的喷发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We knew there might be jets,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.81,0:36:38.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把他表面的物质抛离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}something coming from the surface
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.58,0:36:40.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并围绕土星旋转而形成了E环\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that was injecting material into orbit around Saturn to form the E-ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.43,0:36:45.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,E环离土星最远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The E-ring is furthest from the planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.96,0:36:48.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,约74000英里(120000千米)\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about 74,000 miles away.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.67,0:36:52.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个环绕距离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It happens to be just at the same orbit,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.13,0:36:55.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,刚好约等于土卫二跟土星的距离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the same distance from Saturn as Enceladus.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.29,0:36:58.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此 刚好表明\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so it really suggests
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.02,0:37:01.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,E环来自于土卫二\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that owes its origin to Enceladus.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.69,0:37:05.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,E环的厚度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the thickness of the E-ring
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.10,0:37:07.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,形成它的那些物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sort of matches the thickness
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.44,0:37:11.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都是从土卫二南极喷出的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of particles that were ejected from the South Pole of Enceladus.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.58,0:37:14.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果这些喷泉消失\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If these geysers disappear,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.55,0:37:16.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,E环也会跟着消失\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so might the ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.43,0:37:22.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,喷射水汽表明\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ultimately the liquid jets suggest
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.28,0:37:24.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土卫二含有很多水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that there is water on Enceladus.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.28,0:37:28.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这说明很多问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And perhaps something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.98,0:37:31.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,研究这些水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So the search for water is not,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.18,0:37:34.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不是因为某天我们太渴而要喝这些水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}"Oh, one day we'll be thirsty so we'll have something to drink,"
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.29,0:37:36.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,研究这些水的动力是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the search for water is guided
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.72,0:37:39.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为我们寻找生命的兴趣\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by our interest in the search for life.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.02,0:37:42.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很简单 因为水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's that simple: follow the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.75,0:38:03.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土卫二是最令人激动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Saturn's moon Enceladus is one of the most exciting
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.24,0:38:06.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也是目前太阳系中我们了解最少的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and least understood places in our Solar System.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.29,0:38:09.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土卫二是个奇怪的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Enceladus is a really strange place.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.29,0:38:12.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最奇怪的是它引人注目的明亮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The strangest thing that got people's attention first is it's very bright,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.80,0:38:14.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是太阳系中最明亮的小星体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's the whitest object in the Solar System.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.49,0:38:18.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在我们认识到这都是冰雪覆盖表面的原因\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we now realize that it is covered in freshly fallen snow
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.91,0:38:23.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雪是由落回地面的水汽形成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is the ice that's fallen back from these geysers onto the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.80,0:38:29.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些冰雪让科学家们兴奋\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it's that ice that has scientists excited.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.56,0:38:35.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那里的一切可能性都令人激动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Possibilities there are amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.61,0:38:43.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在太阳系中寻找水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The search for water in our Solar System
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.31,0:38:45.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最终是为了寻找生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is ultimately a search for life.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.78,0:38:48.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,寻找水以期望其中有生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You look for water in the hopes that maybe there will be life.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.10,0:38:54.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由于冰的发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because of the presence of ice,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.02,0:38:57.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一些专家认为外星生物的发现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}some experts believe the search for alien life
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.92,0:38:59.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将从土卫二上开始\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}should begin on Enceladus.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.30,0:39:07.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有很多更令人惊奇的其他物质分子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It has a lot of other molecules in it, a lot of exotic things
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.48,0:39:09.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可能就像这显示的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which show us that there's probably
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.19,0:39:11.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地底下的含水化合物不断运动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}aqueous chemistry going on under ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.38,0:39:15.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果有大量化学反应发生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So there's a lot of little percolating kind of chemistry going on and maybe
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.17,0:39:18.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也许能够进化出生物 因此 我们应该去那看看\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you could get biology, maybe, so maybe we should go look.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.25,0:39:24.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是行星探索的一种圣杯\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is kind of the Holy Grail
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.17,0:39:28.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在现代 出发并寻找\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of modern-day planetary exploration, to go and seek out
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.94,0:39:30.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳系的这些区域\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}those environments in the Solar System
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.55,0:39:32.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些可能拥有生命的区域\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where life might possibly have gotten started.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.65,0:39:34.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后刚好遇见了土卫二\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we just stumbled upon it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.74,0:39:38.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,激动人心？当然了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Is that exciting? Of course it's exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.98,0:39:40.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对于每一位或者的科学家都如此\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's the kind of thing scientists live for.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.74,0:39:43.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能够了解那些气体的成分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We know of the composition of the gases that are coming out
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.95,0:39:46.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是因为我们的太空船穿越其中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because we've flown through them with the spacecraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.10,0:39:49.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那里面包含碳和氮\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we've got the composition including carbon and nitrogen
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.02,0:39:52.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有其他一些生命进化所必需的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and all those goodies that you need to make life.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.35,0:39:54.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们知道这里也有能源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And then we know there's a source of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.18,0:39:56.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由潮汐摩擦带来的热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from the frictional heat of the tidal heat
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.37,0:40:00.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以看见表面冒出来的那些热气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the interior, and we can see the heat on the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.01,0:40:02.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,于是这所有的因素\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So all the elements are there
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.86,0:40:04.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,全部在这里集中以支持生命诞生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that might be sufficient to sustain life
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.68,0:40:06.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果这里真的有的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if life could've got started there.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.78,0:40:09.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是土卫二最令人感兴趣的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So that makes Enceladus a very exciting place.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.10,0:40:15.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过到底是何种形式的生命？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But what kind of life?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.67,0:40:18.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们可不是在谈论寿司\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're not talking sushi,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.65,0:40:24.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不是龙虾和鱼 我们说的是微生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we're not talking lobsters and fish, we're talking microbes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.88,0:40:29.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对于土卫二我想我们最多只能期待这么多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I think that's about the best that we can hope for on a moon like Enceladus.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.60,0:40:33.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你在太阳系内有幸发现一种生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If we ever discover such life in our Solar System, it's gonna be
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.59,0:40:37.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,简单的 像细菌那样的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the simplest possible, it's gonna be bacterial or something like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.98,0:40:42.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即便是发现如此小的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even the discovery of something small,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.14,0:40:47.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那也是非同寻常的大事\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would be a huge event.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.16,0:40:52.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将改变我们对太阳系的认识\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It would change everything that we think and know about our Solar System,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.77,0:40:55.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对宇宙和我们自身的认识\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Universe and ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.39,0:41:03.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大部分对土星和其卫星的了解\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Much of what is known about Saturn and its moons
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.41,0:41:04.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都来源于卡西尼号人造土星卫星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has come from the Cassini satellite,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.66,0:41:08.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,于2004年进入土星轨道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that was inserted into the planet's orbit in 2004.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.97,0:41:18.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,目前正绕着土星旋转 观测土星环 卫星和土星自身\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It is currently touring its rings, moons, and the planet itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.16,0:41:25.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,2008年卡西尼号会绕土星旋转70周\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By 2008, Cassini will have made 70 trips around the gas giant.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.61,0:41:28.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它会在那儿围绕着土星旋转\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Putting an orbiter around the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.22,0:41:30.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,坚守在那儿\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and being able to hang out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.32,0:41:33.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,观测土星系统的任何不同的情况\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and monitor the system and all its different elements
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.01,0:41:35.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在很长一段时间\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for a long period of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.08,0:41:39.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最佳途径就是通过它研究这些星体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's the best way to study these bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.28,0:41:46.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家们需要处理许多日常信息\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists on a daily basis
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.39,0:41:50.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来自于这对"亲密接触"者\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}process the information sent back from these"close encounters".
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.16,0:41:57.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在镜头旁有个雷达\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In addition to the camera there there's a radar
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.00,0:42:00.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,发射无线电波穿过云层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that can send its radiowaves through the clouds
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.50,0:42:03.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后接收表面返回波并绘制图像\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and get an echo of the surface and make an image of the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.74,0:42:06.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,另外使用分光仪测量成分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And there are spectrometers to measure the composition,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.22,0:42:08.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,用红外线设备测量温度\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and other infrared devices to measure temperature.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.70,0:42:11.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是一艘完美的太空船\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So it's a very comprehensive spacecraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.12,0:42:21.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看到更多 了解更多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As you see better, you learn more.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.12,0:42:24.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像瑜伽熊说的那样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I think it may have been Yoghi bear who said,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.75,0:42:27.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只要你认真看 你会发现很多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}"You can see a lot just by looking".
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.69,0:42:31.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把相关信息和地球上比较\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Relating this information to processes on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.96,0:42:35.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有助于解释地球的一些神秘现象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}could help explain mysteries of our own planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.01,0:42:38.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,土星很不同于地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Saturn is really very different from the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.86,0:42:41.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直径比地球大8 9倍\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}its diameter is 8 or 9 times greater than that of the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.91,0:42:43.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,完全由氢气构成的大气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Its atmosphere is made of hydrogen,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.60,0:42:45.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,完全不同于我们的大气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}completely different from our own atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.70,0:42:49.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过同样的物理规律作用着 同样的力量控制这土星气象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the same physics is going on, the same forces are controlling
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.08,0:42:52.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,也控制着地球气象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the weather on Saturn as are controlling the weather on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.34,0:42:57.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是我们历史的一部分 是我们太阳系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It is part of our history, it's the Solar System.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.97,0:43:01.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我开始知道太阳系是如何形成的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So understanding how our Solar System formed
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.76,0:43:03.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,真正知道我为什么在这里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is really understanding how I got here.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.09,0:43:08.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,了解太阳系其他行星的情况\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And understanding the nature of other planets in the Solar System,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.55,0:43:10.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都是我们的邻居\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they're like my neighbours.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.10,0:43:13.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,卡西尼号的新技术\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Cassini's new imaging technologies,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.42,0:43:16.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,让我们看到以前没有看到的景象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are giving us never before seen views and information
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.93,0:43:18.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在每一天\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.85,0:43:21.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,卡西尼号与土星的亲密接触\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Cassini's close encounters with Saturn
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.28,0:43:25.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,带领我们近距离观察它的秘密\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will bring us nearer to unlocking its secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.41,0:43:32.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,很多复杂的事情需要我们很长时间去解释它\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's quite complex and it will take us a long time to figure it all out.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.16,0:43:34.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我想我们现在还不是完全了解土星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I don't think we ever will figure all of it out,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.81,0:43:38.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这真是件愉快的事情 能够环绕和\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but it's just the beauty of being able to be in orbit
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.12,0:43:41.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,观测这样一个富饶的土星系统\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and monitor a rich planetary system like Saturn's.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.24,0:43:49.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球在宇宙中并不孤独\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Earth has a context in the rest of the Universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.61,0:43:52.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你想了解宇宙别处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And, you want to know where we fit in the Universe?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.06,0:43:56.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不要只研究地球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You don't get the answer to that just studying the Earth itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.38,0:44:00.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即使我们已经了解了光环王者很多很多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For, as much as we discover about the Lord of the Rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.68,0:44:03.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它永远激励着我们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it will always inspire us.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.20,0:44:08.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,谢谢观赏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Thanks For Viewing
